theorem P1_iff_P3_of_denseInterior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (interior A)) :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ Topology.P3 A := by
  -- Under the density assumption we have an equivalence between `P3` and `P2`.
  have hP3P2 : Topology.P3 A ↔ Topology.P2 A :=
    Topology.P3_iff_P2_of_denseInterior (X := X) (A := A) hDense
  -- `P1` together with the density of `interior A` yields `P2`.
  have hP1_to_P2 : Topology.P1 A → Topology.P2 A := fun hP1 =>
    Topology.P1_and_denseInterior_implies_P2 (X := X) (A := A) hP1 hDense
  -- `P2` always implies `P1`.
  have hP2_to_P1 : Topology.P2 A → Topology.P1 A :=
    Topology.P2_implies_P1 (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Assemble the forward implication `P1 → P3`.
  have forward : Topology.P1 A → Topology.P3 A := fun hP1 =>
    (hP3P2).2 (hP1_to_P2 hP1)
  -- Assemble the reverse implication `P3 → P1`.
  have backward : Topology.P3 A → Topology.P1 A := fun hP3 =>
    hP2_to_P1 ((hP3P2).1 hP3)
  exact ⟨forward, backward⟩

theorem P1_and_denseInterior_implies_P2 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → Dense (interior A) → Topology.P2 A := by
  intro _ hDenseInt
  exact
    Topology.denseInterior_implies_P2 (X := X) (A := A) hDenseInt
